{
  "stem": "1343.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And those stories actually I remember much longer than the ones that she read from the books.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she was a very charitable lady.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And last sight I had of her was when they took us-- me out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was on one side of the fence, she on the other, and I ran out of the line where we were put in to my mother.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a Gendarme kicked me on one side, and I saw my mother was dragged away from the other side of the fence.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So this was the last of-- the sight I had of her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I have to say that from Gyongyos, we moved to a small town, and this is where we had the lumber yard.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This lumber yard we operated until 1941.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the Jewish laws came out that certain businesses could not be operated by Jews, because they were important for the people's well-being, that time they took it away from us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he moved back to Gyongyos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there, from 1941 to 1944, we lived there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in-- in Gyongyos, there were some 1,200 Jewish souls.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was an orthodox shul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Our Rabbi was [NON-ENGLISH] whose niece is [NON-ENGLISH] in New York who started the Hineni movement.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This is a movement where the [NON-ENGLISH] started to get involved with youth who were getting away from Yiddish guide.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was very successful to bring many of them back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that is about Gyongyos.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the gymnasium, there were some 35 students in a class.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And six of us were Jewish and the rest non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, intimate relationship developed with the Jewish kids much easier and longer-lasting than with the non-Jews, but we did have non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was in the soccer club.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
